h1.a: Extended School Closure and Distance Learning Update

article.div: Keeping our students, staff, and community safe and healthy has been, and continues to be, our top priority. We have now completed the 4th week of school closure and have been working diligently to prepare for distance learning through the remainder of the academic year. While our students will not be coming back to school physically, our commitment to provide learning, enrichment, and support services and resources will continue during the school closure. Please click on Read Full Story for the latest update.

The Franklin-McKinley School District will ensure all 8th grade student graduates have the skills and knowledge to be ready for a college preparatory curriculum in high school. They all will have the ability to pursue a program preparing them for university and/or careers and lifelong learning.
